div1.p:
In the District Court of the 3rd Judicial District Washington Territory, King County. In the application of Alexander S. Hughes Writ of Habeas Corpus
Upon reading as freely the complaint of Alexander S. Hughes, duly signed as ratified by him, wherein to appear that the said Hughes is imprisioned and held by Lewis V. Wyckoff, Sherriff of said County at the County Jail in said county in the Territory of Washington, as further that said Hughes derives to be admitted and jail from which is appears to me that a writ of Habeaus Corpus ought to be granted It is ordered. That a writ of Habeaus Corpus free out of as under the seal of the said Court directed to the said Louis V. Wyckoff Sherrif as aforsaid commanding him to have the body of said Hughes before me at the Court Room on the day of September 1875 at 9 o clock A. M. of that day to so and recieve what shall other as then be reconsidered concerning the said Hughes together with the time and cause of his dentention and that
